The paper focuses on the integration of vision and semantics for visual sensemaking in the context of autonomous driving, which suggests a strong connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of hybrid architectures for perception and control, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed in the paper uses deep learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the significance of human-centered visual sensemaking, which suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) for question-answering and commonsense interpolation.
